  <prompt>
    Remove the `SoftSlashIntentToCapabilityName` dict from both the BFF (Services/Ai/Capabilities/CapabilityRouter.cs:153 or wherever it lives) AND the frontend (SoftSlashRouter — `SOFT_SLASH_TO_INTENT`-style mappings). Per spec FR-20, `commandIntent` bias from task 115 replaces the dict's semantics; integration test asserts slash + NL flows route identically.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform full-stack developer. Comfortable with both BFF C# and React/TypeScript frontend refactoring.</role>

  <goal>
    Backend dict deleted; frontend mapping deleted; integration tests still pass; FR-20 binding test (from task 115) confirms semantic preservation. Grep across `src/` shows zero remaining `SoftSlashIntentToCapabilityName` / `SOFT_SLASH_TO_INTENT` references.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-20 + design WP4. The dict was the legacy bridge between slash-bias and capability-name routing. With task 115's `commandIntent` vector-query bias in place, the dict is dead weight. This task is the cleanup. Note: full `CapabilityRouter` retirement happens in Phase 7 task 141 (atomic deletion of 10 files). This task ONLY removes the dict in advance to prove the bias works in production.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Capabilities/CapabilityRouter.cs</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/SoftSlashRouter.ts (or similar)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/services/</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-20">Dict removed; slash + NL flows produce identical routing for same query text.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Stays inside `Services/Ai/` boundary for BFF removal.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Per-task BFF publish-size measurement; expect MINOR REDUCTION.</constraint>
